				<div class="postbody">
				Recently, one of our newer members said this: 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">for what it's worth...i've been playing this silly game for 4+ years now, and i've been in every kind of guild...small guilds, big guilds, 'family' guilds, 24/7 raiding guilds..... there are much bigger guilds out there who aren't capable of nearly as much as LS. The number one reason why guilds fall apart is bad leadership. i won't name names, but in my experience that's nearly ALWAYS the biggest problem. not recruiting, not 'losing people to raiding guilds', but bad, disorganized leadership. trust me, LS is way way way more organized than any smaller guild i've seen! i've seen us take out some pretty tough mobs without any real problems--and that's not just because of loot, it's because of great raid leadership!!! . </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
If this sounds like the kind of guild you want to belong to, then you should know that Lunar Shadows is recruiting. Qualified applicants must be unguilded, Level 58 with Run 3, able to play their class well, and know how to behave on a raid and in guild chat. (A couple with one member just shy of 58.3 may be considered). 
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.lunarshadows.org/bb2/viewtopic.php?t=2736" target="_blank" class="postlink">Full application requirements and procedure </a>
<br />

<br />
Raiding is encouraged, but voluntary; we do call All Hands On Deck raids where your attendence is strongly encouraged for an important target. We raid approximately 4 times a week, usually around 8-8:30 EST, though times vary. Loot is distributed by a DKP policy, and we do allow guests to accumulate and bid, though member bids have priority. In this way you can raid with us and learn if LS is your kind of guild, and maybe get rewarded. 
<br />

<br />
If you are interested in joining us for grouping or raids, stop by our boards and say hello. Classes we are espcially interested in recruiting are Wizard, warrior, cleric, magician, monk, and bard.
<br />

<br />
See you in the game!<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
